INSTALL

Prerequisites:
--------------

 - Perl 5.10+
 - Elasticsearch 1.1+

Perl Modules:

 - AnyEvent
 - AnyEvent::HTTP
 - Data::Validate::Domain
 - Data::Validate::IP
 - Date::Calc
 - Date::Manip
 - DateTime
 - HTML::Entities
 - HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath
 - JSON
 - List::MoreUtils
 - Modern::Perl 
 - Mojolicious
 - Net::IP::Match::Regexp
 - Net::Twitter
 - Search::Elasticsearch
 - String::Truncate
 - Tie::IxHash
 - URI::Encode
 - URI::Escape
 - WWW::Mechanize
 - Mojolicious::Plugin::Bcrypt

Or, in one big CPAN Minus command:

cpanm Modern::Perl AnyEvent AnyEvent::HTTP File::Spec::Functions Getopt::Long Time::HiRes File::Path Digest::MD5 Search::Elasticsearch HTML::Entities Date::Manip Date::Calc Digest::SHA1 HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath DateTime Net::Twitter WWW::Mechanize Data::Validate::Domain Data::Validate::IP Net::IP::Match::Regexp List::Util String::Truncate List::MoreUtils Digest::MD5 Data::Random Tie::IxHash String::Random URI::Encode Mojolicious::Plugin::Bcrypt Email::MIME Email::Sender::Simple

Setting up:
-----------
You need to set up a twitter API key and enter the credentials into the 
bin/fetch-twitter-api.pl script in order for the twitter function to work.